import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data_grouped['year'], data_grouped['people'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    gender_counts = data.groupby('sex')['people'].sum()
    gender_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('Gender')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution in the population?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    age_sex_population = data.pivot_table(index='age', columns='sex', values='people', aggfunc='sum')
    age_sex_population.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of males and females in the population?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
